  sugar: 22 g
  protein: 15 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 1630 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/edamame-and-cauliflower-fritters-619d017b9fa0be60861115c5
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Asian
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry 
produce (except cauliflower rice). Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size 
pieces if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} and @ginger{1%thumb} 
(all for 4 servings). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites 
from greens; mince whites.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, 
~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @shelled edamame{4%ounce}, garlic, and ginger in a #medium 
microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave for ~{1%minute}. Mash half the edamame lightly 
with a #fork{}. Add @riced cauliflower{6%ounce} and scallion whites; stir to 
combine.

Stir in @tempura batter{82%g}, 1⁄3 cup cold water (2⁄3 cup for 4 servings), 
1/2 tsp salt (1 tsp for 4), and pepper.

> TIP: Batter should be very thick but not dry; add a splash of water if 
> necessary.

Heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil 
is shimmering and hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when added to the 
pan, carefully add 1 1/2 TBSP scoops of batter to pan; press down lightly with 
a #spoon{}. (TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in 
batches.) Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If necessary, heat more oil in pan between batches.

Transfer fritters to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Season with salt.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together roasted broccoli, @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, 
@sesame dressing{1.5%oz}, and half the @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}. Season 
with a pinch of salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and remaining chili 
sauce. Add water 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Divide slaw and fritters between plates. Drizzle chili mayo over fritters. 
Garnish with scallion greens and serve.